sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2069002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RBS + Cpn60 + RBS + CspC + RBS + Antifungal GAFP-1 + double terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This intermediate part allows the transcription of chaperonin 60, CspC and the GAFP-1 protein if added a promoter. This part has a double terminator (T1 E. coli and phage T7 early terminator)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Mara Valverde Rasc??n
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From the parts in the 2016 distribution kit
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No special issues in the design

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K2069000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This intermediate part contains the assemble of Amsterdam's 2011 biobricks for their project icE. coli BBa_K538101 and BBa_K538104

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There were no special issues for the design of this part

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GAFP-1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
The Gastrodia anti-fungal protein (GAFP-1) is a mannose-binding lectin which is able to inhibit the growth of multiples species of plant pathogenic fungi.
The RBS used is a strong RBS for Bacillus subtilis (K780002).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Manon Molina
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This gene was ordered from a synthesis company.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is composed of a Strong RBS (K780002) and the open reading frame of the Gastrodia anti-fungal protein 1 (GAFP-1) optimized for its expression and its secretion in Bacillus subtilis. The codon optimization was made thanks to the DNA 2.0 software program.
